{"legislative_session": "20252026", "identifier": "AB2626", "title": "Housing programs: financing.", "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["bill"], "subject": ["Housingprograms", "financing"], "abstracts": [{"note": "summary", "abstract": "Existing law establishes the Department of Housing and Community Development and requires it to administer various programs intended to promote the development of housing, as specified, pursuant to which the department provides financial assistance in the form of deferred payment loans to pay for the eligible costs of development of specified types of housing projects. Existing law sets forth various general powers of the department in implementing these programs, including authorizing the department to enter into long-term contracts or agreements of up to 30 years for the purpose of servicing loans or grants or enforcing regulatory agreements or other security documents.\n\nThis bill would permit the department to waive payment of residual receipts or minimum annual loan payments required under a department regulatory agreement."}], "other_titles": [], "other_identifiers": [{"identifier": "ocd-bill-ca-20252026-ab2626"}], "actions": [{"description": "Read first time. To print.", "date": "2026-02-20", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["reading-1"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "From printer. May be heard in committee March 23.", "date": "2026-02-21", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": [], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Referred to Com. on H. & C.D.", "date": "2026-03-09", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["referral-committee"], "related_entities": [{"name": "Com. on H. & C.D.", "entity_type": "organization", "organization_id": null}]}, {"description": "From committee chair, with author's amendments: Amend, and re-refer to Com. on H. & C.D. Read second time